00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:45,009
She knew what she needed to do.

274
00:14:45,009 --> 00:14:47,428
Luckily for me, I
figured into her plans.

275
00:14:47,428 --> 00:14:50,807
Our hearts were
beating like crazy.

276
00:14:50,807 --> 00:14:53,476
This before or after
you left the cell?

277
00:14:53,476 --> 00:14:54,477
(growling)

278
00:14:54,477 --> 00:14:56,354
Just let me finish, will you?

279
00:14:58,773 --> 00:15:01,025
(bats squeaking)

280
00:15:01,025 --> 00:15:01,984
Cornelia!

281
00:15:01,984 --> 00:15:03,361
I order you to step away!

282
00:15:03,361 --> 00:15:05,905
Uh‐uh.

283
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:07,990
Cornelia, I am warning you,

284
00:15:07,990 --> 00:15:09,784
step aside!

285
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,621
(gunfire)

286
00:15:16,374 --> 00:15:18,126
No, Cornelia!

287
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:23,506
We barely knew each other,

288
00:15:23,506 --> 00:15:26,217
Cornelia protected me
and she died for it.

289
00:15:26,217 --> 00:15:29,804
Or that's what I‐‐
I always thought.

290
00:15:29,804 --> 00:15:31,889
I had no idea, Lupin, sorry.

291
00:15:31,889 --> 00:15:34,892
It's all right, Jigen, but
I gotta take a little trip.

292
00:15:34,892 --> 00:15:38,271
Just leave
everything here to us.

293
00:15:38,271 --> 00:15:52,076
♪

294
00:15:52,076 --> 00:15:53,661
Lupin.

295
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:56,122
Why does that name
seem to haunt me?

296
00:15:56,122 --> 00:15:58,583
(groaning)

297
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:02,003
Feeling better?

298
00:16:02,003 --> 00:16:05,214
Sergio, please tell me,
who is this man Lupin?

299
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:09,510
He seems so certain he
knows me, and every time...

300
00:16:09,510 --> 00:16:11,429
It's as if my brain is cramping,

301
00:16:11,429 --> 00:16:15,725
as if even the thought of him
were like poison or something.

302
00:16:15,725 --> 00:16:16,976
It's true.

303
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:18,895
Yes, you did know
each other once,

304
00:16:18,895 --> 00:16:21,606
and I regret to say that it
doesn't surprise me to hear

305
00:16:21,606 --> 00:16:24,192
that the recollection
of it is causing angst.

306
00:16:24,192 --> 00:16:26,819
What on earth do you
mean by that, Sergio?

307
00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:29,906
I beg of you, Sergio, go on.

308
00:16:29,906 --> 00:16:31,490
It's, I...

309
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:35,369
I can't tell you.

310
00:16:35,369 --> 00:16:36,996
Cornelia!

311
00:16:44,587 --> 00:16:47,048
(gears cranking)

312
00:16:49,926 --> 00:16:50,968
Hm.

313
00:16:55,139 --> 00:16:56,974
Father.

314
00:16:56,974 --> 00:16:59,018
What's this all
about, you must tell me.

315
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:01,812
If something happened in the
past between me and this man,

316
00:17:01,812 --> 00:17:04,398
it's important that I know.

317
00:17:04,398 --> 00:17:06,275
Very well, then.

318
00:17:06,275 --> 00:17:09,278
Are you quite sure about this?

319
00:17:09,278 --> 00:17:10,655
Yes.

320
00:17:12,573 --> 00:17:15,451
He was a petty thief who broke
into the compound one night.

321
00:17:15,451 --> 00:17:16,661
You were just a girl.

322
00:17:16,661 --> 00:17:18,788
He was detected
immediately, of course.

323
00:17:18,788 --> 00:17:20,706
But like a cornered
animal snatching wildly

324
00:17:20,706 --> 00:17:23,459
at whatever might save him,
he took you as a hostage.

325
00:17:23,459 --> 00:17:25,253
As he made his death blood bid

326
00:17:25,253 --> 00:17:27,380
to outrun us to
the compound wall.

327
00:17:27,380 --> 00:17:30,299
I can still hear your frightened
voice calling out to me.

328
00:17:30,299 --> 00:17:32,051
Father, help me!

329
00:17:32,051 --> 00:17:33,052
Then...

330
00:17:33,052 --> 00:17:35,054
(Cornelia shrieking)

331
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:37,598
...then we caught up with him.

332
00:17:37,598 --> 00:17:39,183
The vindictive schweinhund!

333
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:42,311
He knew her father would
never forgive, and so he...

334
00:17:42,311 --> 00:17:44,647
(gunfire)

335
00:17:44,647 --> 00:17:46,357
Right in front of me.

336
00:17:46,357 --> 00:17:50,987
♪

337
00:17:50,987 --> 00:17:54,407
You died calling my name.

338
00:17:54,407 --> 00:17:57,743
That is how you know each other.

339
00:17:57,743 --> 00:17:59,537
But there's more.

340
00:17:59,537 --> 00:18:03,874
A miracle, animated by the
implacable spear of justice,

341
00:18:03,874 --> 00:18:08,254
you awoke from death, reborn
as an angel of vengeance.

342
00:18:11,882 --> 00:18:13,551
Now that you know the truth,

343
00:18:13,551 --> 00:18:16,095
there can be no
business before this.

344
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:17,930
It is your destiny.

345
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:21,267
Summon your
legions of the dead.

346
00:18:21,267 --> 00:18:24,228
Command them to seek out
and conscript into the ranks

347
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:26,606
the people who robbed
you of your young life!

348
00:18:26,606 --> 00:18:28,608
(guttural moaning)

349
00:18:30,401 --> 00:18:32,945
(growling)

350
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:40,494
♪

351
00:18:40,494 --> 00:18:41,662
It's around here somewhere.

352
00:18:43,664 --> 00:18:46,167
You mean the cemetery?

353
00:18:46,167 --> 00:18:49,128
Yeah, I figured digging up
a grave is sort of step one.

354
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:52,465
I mean, that's where
I would start, anyway.

355
00:18:52,465 --> 00:18:53,507
Not that I could ever imagine

356
00:18:53,507 --> 00:18:56,552
doing something
like that, though.

357
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:58,387
None of this bodes well at all.

358
00:19:01,974 --> 00:19:03,184
There it is.

359
00:19:04,935 --> 00:19:15,154
♪

360
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:18,324
Honest to God, I don't know
what the worst scenario is,

361
00:19:18,324 --> 00:19:22,870
that she's alive and doesn't
remember me or she's here.

362
00:19:26,707 --> 00:19:27,750
This has...

363
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:32,380
Wait.

364
00:19:32,380 --> 00:19:35,257
This has been dug up.

365
00:19:35,257 --> 00:19:36,467
But, why?

366
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:38,260
(grunts)

367
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:52,858
♪

368
00:19:56,904 --> 00:19:58,072
Huh?

369
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:04,704
♪

370
00:20:04,704 --> 00:20:06,414
But...

371
00:20:06,414 --> 00:20:11,627
♪

372
00:20:11,627 --> 00:20:13,295
Cornelia!

373
00:20:19,176 --> 00:20:21,345
That must be it.

374
00:20:21,345 --> 00:20:23,013
Are we going to break in?

375
00:20:23,013 --> 00:20:25,391
I prefer to call
it "dropping by."

376
00:20:33,065 --> 00:20:35,568
♪

377
00:20:35,568 --> 00:20:37,319
Jigen, what happened?

378
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:39,071
(growling)

379
00:20:39,071 --> 00:20:42,199
♪

380
00:20:42,199 --> 00:20:43,367
What the‐‐?

381
00:20:43,367 --> 00:20:46,871
♪

382
00:20:46,871 --> 00:20:49,874
Goemon, put that damn
thing to use, will you?

383
00:20:49,874 --> 00:20:50,916
Thanks, I needed that.

384
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:52,918
‐Sorry.
‐Any time.

385
00:20:52,918 --> 00:20:55,546
If these guys are what
I think they are, well,

386
00:20:55,546 --> 00:20:58,966
killing them might
be a little redundant.

387
00:20:58,966 --> 00:21:01,427
(screeching)

388
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:05,848
(screaming)

389
00:21:06,682 --> 00:21:07,808
Jigen!

390
00:21:07,808 --> 00:21:11,562
♪

391
00:21:11,562 --> 00:21:13,856
I'm okay, it's weird,
it didn't burn me.

392
00:21:13,856 --> 00:21:16,317
But when...

393
00:21:16,317 --> 00:21:18,652
It's on you, it's
like you can't breathe.

394
00:21:18,652 --> 00:21:21,113
(panting)

395
00:21:23,699 --> 00:21:27,661
So, what in the name of
hell are those things?

396
00:21:27,661 --> 00:21:42,426
♪

397
00:21:42,426 --> 00:21:43,886
What do you know.

398
00:21:43,886 --> 00:21:47,139
I guess they're not
zombies, after all.

399
00:21:47,139 --> 00:21:49,099
Uh, hold that thought.

400
00:21:49,099 --> 00:21:58,818
♪

401
00:21:58,818 --> 00:22:01,904
How many times do I gotta
tell you, use the sharp end?

402
00:22:01,904 --> 00:22:03,781
Very funny, and did
you miss them all?

403
00:22:03,781 --> 00:22:06,450
There isn't a drop of
blood on my sword.

404
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:08,369
I was right the first time.

405
00:22:08,369 --> 00:22:10,788
♪

406
00:22:10,788 --> 00:22:12,331
Jigen, wait,
where are you going?

407
00:22:12,331 --> 00:22:14,625
I have absolutely
no freaking idea!

408
00:22:14,625 --> 00:22:16,335
Do you mind if I come along?

409
00:22:21,966 --> 00:22:24,718
Was I dreaming or was
that Jigen and Goemon?

410
00:22:24,718 --> 00:22:26,887
That's asking too much.

411
00:22:30,307 --> 00:22:32,768
(hissing)

412
00:22:34,478 --> 00:22:38,023
It's a fortunate thing that
we took that girl alive,

413
00:22:38,023 --> 00:22:40,109
now he will come to me!

414
00:22:40,109 --> 00:23:05,467
♪

415
00:23:10,347 --> 00:23:12,558
♪ Lupin the 3rd ♪♪

416
00:23:12,558 --> 00:23:14,268
Fujiko thinks
she's got it tough,

417
00:23:14,268 --> 00:23:15,811
but I'm the one with the
vengeful ex who happens

418
00:23:15,811 --> 00:23:17,313
to be the queen of the zombies.

419
00:23:17,313 --> 00:23:18,939
Where the hell do you
hide from guys like that?

420
00:23:18,939 --> 00:23:20,524
Okay, maybe a coffin
was a bad choice,

421
00:23:20,524 --> 00:23:22,192
but you try thinking
straight when everyone

422
00:23:22,192 --> 00:23:24,194
and his undead brother
wants a piece of you.

423
00:23:24,194 --> 00:23:26,488
Where's Jigen, where's Goemon,
where's it all gonna end?

424
00:23:26,488 --> 00:23:30,159
Catch you next time in "The
Second Time Around, Part 2."

425
00:23:30,159 --> 00:24:38,978
♪

